      <name>jQuery &lt; 3.4.0 Object Extensions Vulnerability</name>
      <modification_time>2026-01-26T05:23:25Z</modification_time>
      <comment />
      <creation_time>2026-01-26T05:23:25Z</creation_time>
      <host>127.0.0.1<asset asset_id="bb3bcf7b-ed9f-4105-8e8f-34afbd3a9eeb" /><hostname>host1.example.com</hostname></host>
      <port>80/tcp</port>
      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.142314">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>jQuery &lt; 3.4.0 Object Extensions Vulnerability</name>
        <family>Web application abuses</family>
        <cvss_base>6.1</cvss_base>
        <severities score="6.1">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2021-07-20T23:15:00Z</date>
            <score>6.1</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=jQuery is prone to multiple vulnerabilities regarding property
  injection in Object.prototype.|insight=The following flaws exist:

  - CVE-2019-5428: A prototype pollution vulnerability exists that allows an attacker to inject
  properties on Object.prototype.

  - CVE-2019-11358: jQuery mishandles jQuery.extend(true, {}, ...) because of Object.prototype
  pollution. If an unsanitized source object contained an enumerable __proto__ property, it could
  extend the native Object.prototype.|affected=jQuery prior to version 3.4.0.|impact=|solution=Update to version 3.4.0 or later. Patch diffs are available for
  older versions.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 3.4.0 or later. Patch diffs are available for
  older versions.</solution>
